Stackmob Java SDK 1.0.0 API

This SDK contains all the tools you need to build a painlessly network connected app with java.

See:
          Description

Packages
com.stackmob.sdk.api Classes for communicating directly with StackMob.
com.stackmob.sdk.callback The various callbacks used to respond to asynchronous calls.
com.stackmob.sdk.exception StackMob specific exceptions.
com.stackmob.sdk.model Base classes for objects that map to StackMob data.
com.stackmob.sdk.push Support classes for push methods.

 

This SDK contains all the tools you need to build a painlessly network connected app with java. It's primarily meant for inclusion in StackMob's Android SDK, but can be used by itself anywhere java is supported, including on the desktop.

Classes to Check Out

  • StackMobModel The base class for data models
  • StackMobUser The base class for data models representing users, with user authentication methods
  • StackMob Low level user authentication methods
  • StackMobDatastoreLow level data methods
  • StackMobPushLow level push methods
